<http://www.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/event/50601AKRTTBVBCHPTJTHBMBPVLKRJDRHP>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Building Character On Stage Camp";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">Tidemark Youth Theatre Arts: Building Character on Stage</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Step into the spotlight this Spring Break!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The Tidemark Youth Theatre Arts Camp invites young performers to explore creativity, confidence, and storytelling on the big stage at the Tidemark Theatre. Over five exciting days, participants will dive into the world of theatre through acting games, improvisation, movement, and collaborative storytelling in a fun and supportive environment.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Led by experienced theatre instructors, campers will build performance skills including character development, vocal projection, stage presence, and teamwork - all while making new friends and discovering the joy of live performance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The week wraps up with a special mini-showcase where students share what they’ve created with family and friends on the Tidemark stage.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Whether your child is brand new to theatre or already loves to perform, this camp is a welcoming space to imagine, play, and grow as a performer.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\"><span class=\"ItalicText\">Recommended for youth ages 9–14.</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Instructor: Heather Gordon Murphy</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Heather Gordon Murphy is an experienced dance and movement artist, choreographer, and creative director based in Campbell River. She has worked extensively with local theatre organizations including Shoreline Musical Theatre Society, Rivercity Players, and the Tidemark Youth Theatre Arts program. Internationally, Heather served as Assistant Choreographer for both the 2010 Olympic Opening and Closing Ceremonies and the FIFA World Cup Opening Ceremonies in Azerbaijan presented by Cirque du Soleil.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>As Artistic Director and Co-Owner of RainCoast School of Musical Theatre, Heather is passionate about helping young performers build confidence and explore creativity through movement, storytelling, and performance. Her energetic and supportive teaching style inspires participants to take creative risks and discover new ways to express themselves on stage.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">This program is generously supported by the Rotary Club of Campbell River.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>📅 March 23–27, 2026<span><br/></span>🕘 9:00 AM – 2:00 PM daily<span><br/></span>📍 Tidemark Theatre<span><br/></span>🎟️ Registration:$188.00 <span class=\"ItalicText\">(+applicable taxes and fees)</span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-03-23T09:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/files/ab884b0d-91fd-4213-9971-5c1b2aeb16a0.jpg>;
