<http://www.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/event/53001ACMLBMKGCRKLTKVJLVJTHVVQTDSS>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Dancing with Tapas";
  schema:description """
	Imagine this: you and your friends make a night of it—gather together for Dancing with Tapas, savour incredible food, enjoy the music, share laughter… and at the same time, a teenager in Kenya gains mobility.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>He has been housebound for the past three years because his mother can no longer carry him. Your night out can help change that—for him, and for many others. Just imagine the difference your evening can make.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This vibrant evening brings together some of the region’s favourite culinary talents. Enjoy tapas-style offerings from Pho54, Baan Thai, Royal Aroma, and Naturally Pacific Carve Kitchen & Meatery, with a sweet finish from Stonehouse Teas. Each vendor will be serving a curated selection of their menu favourites.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Purchase tokens to sample dishes, sip beverages, and explore everything the evening has to offer.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>From 6:00–8:00 PM, indulge in delicious bites, browse the silent auction, and take part in the always-entertaining Paper Airplane Toss—where you could win an unforgettable 20-minute helicopter ride for 3–4 people, courtesy of 49 North Helicopters.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The excitement continues at 8:00 PM with the Paper Airplane Toss finals on the dance floor, plus your chance to win a 5-night Discovery Islands cruise for two, and bid on exclusive live auction items—including Canucks box seats and an incredible Fall Feast for 12.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Then at 9:00 PM, the dance floor comes alive as Time Well Wasted, an electrifying 11-piece band from the Comox Valley, takes the stage. With classic rock, funk, and R&B favourites—complete with a dynamic horn section and rich vocal harmonies—you won’t want to sit down.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Come for the food. Stay for the music. Leave knowing you’ve helped change a life.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets:$60.00 Admission <span class=\"ItalicText\">(+applicable taxes & fees)</span>
""";
