<http://www.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/event/38001AJMJGLMVGBGPDQNMJJMCJDLNBDQB>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Fat Joke";
  schema:description """
	<span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">An unfiltered, hilarious interrogation of fatphobia.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>A mixture of stand-up comedy, storytelling, and fact-blasting, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Fat Joke</span> puts fatphobia under the spotlight. Drawing upon personal experience and research, comedian, actor, and writer Cheyenne Rouleau dissects this often-untalked-about topic with eviscerating wit. Think: <span class=\"ItalicText\">Nanette</span> by Hannah Gadsby meets <span class=\"ItalicText\">Inside</span> by Bo Burnham. This one-person show invites us to confront assumptions. It’s all the stuff people don’t feel comfortable talking about turned into a comedy show!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“As a fat person, I never thought of myself as ‘sexy.’ Society never allowed me to be. So I got funny.”—Cheyenne Rouleau<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Recommended Age:</span>  16+<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Content Warning:</span><span><br/></span>This show contains significant discussion of fatphobia and diet culture. Additionally, it contains sensitive themes, mentions of abortions, complicated pregnancies, slavery, eugenics, racism, systemic oppression, and sexual assault. And it’s really funny. Promise.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets: $28.00 Members, $33.00 Non-Members <span class=\"ItalicText\">(+applicable taxes & fees)</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Your comfort matters to us. To help every guest enjoy the show, the Tidemark Theatre offers several seating options:<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Hercules Chairs</span><span><br/></span>We have a limited number of Hercules chairs designed for larger bodies and folks who prefer more room. These chairs are 23.5\" x 31.25\", 17.5\" high from the floor, and support up to 453 kg.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Standard Seats (Multiple Widths)</span><span><br/></span>Our theatre seats come in 19\", 20\", and 21\" widths. When choosing seats online, hover over each seat on the map to see its width and select what works best for you.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Wheelchair Seating</span><span><br/></span>For wheelchair-accessible seating, please reach out to the box office so we can make sure you’re set up comfortably.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Have questions or need support? Our box office team is happy to help you find the best seating option.
""";
