<http://www.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/event/51601ASNDVBQVGLKLVCBQNQGNVJJTVQBG>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "QI Festival of Chamber Music Pass";
  schema:description """
	Quadra Island Festival of Chamber Music was founded in 2011, and provides Islanders with a week of exquisite music performed by international-renowned musicians. This annual event is held at beautiful local venues including the Quadra Island United Church as well as the SouthEnd Winery Farm concert which is only available with our <span class=\"BoldText\">Bundled Ticket Package.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">SERENADE:</span><span class=\"BoldText\"> Monday, June 22nd  7:00 pm </span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Cape Mudge Church</span><span><br/></span>Ludwig van Beethoven: <span class=\"ItalicText\">Serenade</span>, opus 25 for flute, violin and viola<span><br/></span>Gabriel Faur? and Camille Saint-Sa?ns: works for cello and harp<span><br/></span>Vincent Persichetti: <span class=\"ItalicText\">Serenade</span> for flute and harp<span><br/></span>Philip Glass: String Quartet no. 3<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">INTIMATE CONVERSATIONS:</span><span class=\"BoldText\"> Tuesday, June 23rd  7:00 pm </span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Quadra Community Centre</span><span><br/></span>Paul Reade: Suite for clarinet and harp<span><br/></span>Claude Debussy: Trio for flute, viola and harp<span><br/></span>Franz Schubert: Trio in E-flat Major for violin, cello and piano<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">A CLASSICAL PANORAMA:</span><span class=\"BoldText\"> Thursday, June 25th  7:00 pm  </span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Southend Farm Winery</span><span><br/></span>Astor Piazzolla: works for cello and accordion<span><br/></span>Giacchino Rossini: Quartet for flute and string trio<span><br/></span>Kasper Kummer: Duet for flute and clarinet<span><br/></span>Toshiro Mayuzumi: <span class=\"ItalicText\">Bunraku</span> for solo cello<span><br/></span>A new work by Philip Hansen, Festival artistic director<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">SPARK, SHADOW and SHIMMER: </span><span class=\"BoldText\">Friday, June 26th  7:00 pm </span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Quadra Community Centre</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\"> </span>W.A. Mozart: Quintet in C Major for two violins, two violas and cello<span><br/></span>Max Bruch: Selections from Eight Pieces for viola, clarinet and piano<span><br/></span>Maurice Ravel: <span class=\"ItalicText\">Introduction & Allegro</span> for harp and ensemble<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Bundled Tickets</span>: $125.00 for all 4 concerts <span class=\"ItalicText\">(+applicable taxes & fees)<span class=\"BoldText\"> Limited Availability</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For more information on the exceptional talent playing this year's festival and photos from last years performances, please visit <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.quadrafestival.ca/\">https://www.quadrafestival.ca/</a>
""";
